\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 No, I - Maesteg, but I don't remember - as I told you before my father came from Ma
esteg, they used to have little concerts you know, I remember - I remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Was this while you were still in school, while you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Yes. I remember singing in a little concert - I
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Cinema while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 
Oh yes, not much. My brother - my eldest brother I suppose - when he started working, my mother thought the world of him, and I suppose that - she used to give him a shilling po
cket money when he started working, and my father wasn't well, and there wasn't much money then, every fortnight or something isn't it they were having their - and I suppose I've heard my mother say that my brother John offered the sixpence back to her - 
if he didn't have anything. So that showed that he hadn't spent the shilling you see. So he offered her the sixpence back. If - you know, if she was short, if she didn't have anything, so I've heard my mother say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 So you didn't have regular pocket money when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 They wouldn't give you a ha'penny a week or a penny a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Oh yes, we'd have a ha'penny and we'd have a lot for that then wouldn't we, on a Saturday. Saturday. We used to have -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Your father would give it to you every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Mm. We'd have - you know, something on a Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 You don't remember how much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Oh ha'penny, or a penny.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Would you have it every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Mostly. Mm. Or you know - if man would buy in the Co-op isn't it, she'd buy something there for us and give it to us when we come in.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 What would you spend the money on if you had money yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Oh dear, on all - we used to have - what - Spanish, what you call Spanish sometimes, and butterscotch isn't it or something
 like that now you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Sweets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Yes, oh yes, mm. There was an old lady - Betty we used to call her, she had a little shop, and she had a drawer, and you'd ask }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8729985\charrsid12984966 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966  hapenny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8729985\charrsid12984966  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 worth from the drawer, you know she used to keep the drawer, and she'd ope
n that up then of course you could choose what you liked from there. Some of the boys of course often she wasn't - couldn't see very well - the boys you know often you know used to take more than those coming to them you see. And Jim was one, you know he 
w
as awful at teasing her. And anyway - she had a - we'd have a hapennyworth from the drawer we used to call then, and on - on a Neath Fair Day, she used to hold a stall - up on the field, and they'd go from Maesteg you know then early in the morning, and F
fair Beti we used to call it, and she used to make a - a little care that day and bring a big stall out and have somebody to help her, and we'd be going up there that was a - a day out, on the Neath Fair Day. Up on the field.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 You wouldn't go to the fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 No, no, up on the moun - and then - yes, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8729985\charrsid12984966 and we used to c}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 atch them you know, going in in the morning, my brother used to get up at six o'clock in the morning to see the horses going in and everything, pigs and all that you know, they'd go from Mae
steg, pass - through Pon - through Bryn, and up to - walk to Pontrydyfen after then to - to Neath Fair then, and then we used to come under on the - watch them coming back and we'd shout Feirin o'r ffair, feirin o'r ffair, and perhaps someone would throw 
us a pear or a plum.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after her house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Yes, before my sisters came old enough just to help her to wash and - you know, her washing day. That's all I remember. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Relations, friends or neighbours, would they come and help at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Yes, friends and relations sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 What would they do, in what way would they help?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Well with the washing. Washing. And I don't know what about ironing and - of course there wasn't so 
much ironing - and yet there were with the pinafores and things like that we used to wear then. For my sisters older than me - and - the cleaning, I don't know, 'cos - my mother was a pretty - healthy woman I think you know, she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 If she was ill or when she was confined to bed, she'd be having a baby you see, she'd have to be in bed then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 How did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Well - help coming in then you know, and the neighbours next door, she'd be with - they'd come in you know, there'd be t
wo ladies there, two friends there, they'd come in, and then my mother would be in when - she when they'd have the baby. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Do you remember what happened when one of your younger brothers or sisters was born? Can you remember one of them being born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 
Yes, I for, but - that was up in Bryn Gurnos Street mind. Yes, and he was born on - the Baptist big meeting I suppose, and - there was a noted old preacher then was Robert Allyn, and it was he who was preaching a - and I suppose he called in to see m
y mother. Mm. Our - or - yes, our I for was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Do you remember then the day and what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 
Yes, I think I - you know, well I was ten then see wasn't I? Mm. And going up to see him of course isn't it. I wanted to nurse him - naturally isn't it. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Would somebody come in then to help, the neighbours would be in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 
Well of course and - you would take - if there was - if I was ten, well my sisters would be much older then wouldn't they. They were there to help that time see weren't they,
 and - yes, yes. 'Cos - Mary, yes, yes, oh no, when Gwennie was born Mary was there, you know, she got married then when - Gwennie was born but she was there when Gwennie was born with my mother. And Sue of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Did any of your parents have relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Your father and your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 
Yes, my father's - brother - was living, and he - they were a big family. But - I don't think there was many of my mother's because she was - they were in Maesteg you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 How much did you see of them? Of the relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Well - my mother's sister - used to come - now and again you know for the day, and - and - just for the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 What about your father's people living in Bryn, did you see much of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 No, well of 
course we were in school together, you know, all of us, and - my - my eldest sister, and them were very friendly. Of course you know well - they were younger than me - they were older than me really, but there's Uncle Willie now as you know, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 You used to see a lot of them really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 
Oh yes, well of course, we've been brought up together, and - the oldest daughter - did I tell you that my mother took Enid didn't I. Well - it was one of those daughters that my mother took the baby for six weeks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Of your father's brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Of my father - yes, father's brother's daughter. - Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Why did she take her for six weeks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 She was ill, she had - when the baby was born - and she had - six others, she had seven girls, and she was taken very
 ill and she had to - I don't know, so she couldn't look after the baby so my mother took the baby for six weeks. Yes. Mm. Yes. And my mother had reared another one - she - for six years, my father's people again. They were living in Neath, and - the moth
er and father died, and I think, did you hear me say - you know, the - the - when we used to go to Tonmawr I was telling you, well her - my aunt's daughter - and she couldn't take her because she had this invalid then. So my mother took her for six years.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Was that when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Yes, at home, yes, our - but our Sal was home then, and she did - she did for her. She was very good with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 How old was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Well a baby. Yes, yes, well a couple of months old she was and she had her for six years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 What happened to her then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 
Oh she went then - when - when she got old enough, when she went then - she went back to her grandmother then, to Tonmawr, they took her then you know, when - the daughter that was the same age as me, ca
me home, you know, from school, and she was able to look after her then, so she went to Tonmawr with her grandmother. Mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Oh yes. Mm, I remember one old lady coming up - she was a widow and every time she'd go
 out she'd say - thanks very much for my place, she'd say you know, she was a widow. Her husband was from the Graw Valley, I remember her saying that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Where would they see their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Oh they'd come to our house or they'd go there. One my mot
her was very friendly - with - with a - a - Cilcarn Farm, and she used to go up and visit them, to Cilcarn Farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Did your father and mother have the same friends? The people in Cilcarn Farm, were they particularly your mother's friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Yes, and of course - my brother married one of the daughters, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Did your father and mother have separate friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Oh well of course - they were very friendly with all the farmers there. And the funny thing - they were all Methodist. All the farme
rs round there then. I could name the farms for you you know, but they were all - they were all Methodist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 They tended to have their friends in the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Oh yes, yes, and the - the - secretary of the chapel - was a friend of theirs, and his wi
fe was our - schoolmistress. Mrs Joseph, she was our headmistress you know - ever since we remember she was teaching John and Mary and all of them, and me, you know so we were all friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 And mainly your father and mother saw their friends in your house, they went to visit as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Oh - oh yes, yes, not much mind, they'd never go out much you know. No. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 People tended to come and see them did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Were friends ever invited into the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Well, as you sa
y you know, the - they - they were friends with them in the Garw and the Gilva, and they used to come and visit us you know now and again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 For the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Were they offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Oh yes. Oh yes, they'd have a - a high tea in the front room when they come. Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 They'd use the front room for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 
Mm. Yes. And then of course - and - well when we killed a pig of course it was house was full then helping and all that you know. That was a very interesting time when we killed a pig. Mm. Oh yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 You'd have all the people in would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Well, of course some to help you know, and then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 To cut up you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Oh no, the butcher was doing that you know. But - all - we were a lot - there we
re - several of our - family married then, and the day of the cutting up - my mother was putting the pieces for everyone you know, and - say if - we kill a pig one - you know, one - one week, then we'd have give a piece to the man that would be - killing 
the next - pig you know, that's how they were, when they were killing pigs they'd give pieces for one another you know, like - sharing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 That was the payment was it instead of money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Yes, yes, no, you know, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 No money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 No
. No, if - well Mr Thomas now, Joe Thomas, he'd kill a pig, of course there was a piece for us. And - but my mother was like this - oh so and so is not well, I'd better give him - a bit of - of meat. Right. There was an old gent up - Billie Perkins I reme
m
ber his name was, and he wasn't well. And this old widow now was with him, he said, well I want to send them a bit, right. There was another - old lady, she wasn't well, right. I'd better send her a little bit. There was a young man - living - Tom Nichola
s
 this was, going in for preaching he was, but he wasn't well, well, right, a little bit for him. So by the time she shared it out all, very little we had. And my brother now, the day of the killing the pig you see, we'd make faggots for the - next day now
,
 and those would be ready. And I used to help mam to make the faggots, and we'd start giving them the faggots and my mother would ask, Arthur do you want another one? Yes, he said. I'd better have another one, he said to make sure of this because we won't
 see much of the pork. And - oh dear -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 So it was a special occasion really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Would the people who came in now about it would they have something to eat and drink with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Oh the butcher. The butcher see, and of course the men would be round you know there they'd go to their own homes really. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Would you say that the friends invited in to your house were your mother's friends or your father's friends, or friends of both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Well - both of them really. Only when my
 mother's - people would come isn't it you know, and - my father's sister that lived in Tonmawr, and my mother, were very very close. They were more like sisters really, than - than - sister-in-laws, they were very - and she was a lovely person. Oh humble
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Did friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 
Well - yes, they would, you know, the old man that used to keep the chapel house now I think of - she'd come up you know, and - Marie you know, they would never say Mrs then, Mrs Oban and Mrs 
Stanforth. Marie and all that you know, we've been in chapel, if my father was you know - the leader for the week or for the month what you say, he'd never say - Mrs Stanforth. Marie, have you got a word to say tonight, or something like that you know, th
ey'd never Mr and Mrs would they. Oh yes, we had - my mother and father had very lovely friends. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Would neighbours come in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Yes, especially when we lived in the - in Coalyard Row, in the small - when we were born you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Nore so than Bryn Gurnos Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 
Oh yes, because they were like one - you know - one another, in and out one another's homes you know and helping one another there, I remember that very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 More of a community there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Yes, more, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Why was that I wonder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 
Well - of course we were - in a street then - we were the corner house, now we were a corner house here, but - a road between us, on the whole we were very friendly with the man next door, and when he 
buried his wife I had to go in to work with him, and do his washing and all. I used to do his washing. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Did your friends go out often to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Oh no. No. I remember them going once - with my aunt - and her husband, this
 one now that came with the - children, you know, they came on right after, and they wanted my mother and father to come with them for a day to Chepstow. I think it was Chepstow. Anyway they were going down the hill in Chepstow I suppose, and - they were 
n
ot - je wasn't - they were not very - what do you say, churchgoers or anything like that you know and she sent the children but they were not going. And - they were going down Chepstow hill I suppose, and something went wrong in the car. And it was a mira
c
le that they were all alive. And my uncle said then that if it wasn't for my mother and father, with them, that they would never have been saved, because they were - you know, he thought that they were better than them, that they were saved through my mot
her and father. I remember them saying that. Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 
People often say now that you know in those days they made their own amusements years ago, do you think that your parents what do you think your parents did if they'd go went to somebody else's house
 you know, on the rare occasions they went, would they make music or play games or would they just chat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 
No, I don't think so. Just chat you know, that's all, oh no. And I do remember my mother and father going out a lot really, because when I tell y
ou when my father was working, when they had a Co-operative you know, under the colliery, they used to go there to help, my father on turns. Well - well he'd have to do that and the gardening see at home, I mean it wouldn't be really -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Would his turn come very often to serve in that shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Yes, and I don't know how often it would come then you know, no. But I remember, you know, them doing it.
