\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Yes, I don't know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 And about six on his as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 
Yes. I should think so, I don't remember anyway I remember the - the - the table laid now in the front room. So many as could go round that see, and then the others after. Well my - my - granny Cook as I sa
y, my father's sisters was living in Tonmawr - on the wedding morning now she said to me, now - don't forget to kiss your mother - before you go. So I went to kiss my mother - the morning - before - before going out and she went to cry and I did, and I co
uldn't go out for a spell 'cos I was crying. 'Til my brother said, now, come on. And we all had to go, but I was crying - before I went out. 'Cos I saw my mother crying. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 The wedding day isn't it. You went down to Grove Place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Yes. Got marr
ied at Grove Place. I had two bridesmaids. And a flower girl. Mm. Then of course after we got married we went back to the house to Bryn, and had breakfast. And - so many round the table, so many as could go then of course, there was others there, but - th
en as soon as we had breakfast and I changed - and - then we were going away - to Aberystwyth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 The people who came to the wedding, how were they invited? Did you ask them?
