Oh yes, some of them now you see but my - the headmistress now was very fond of my brother-in-law, Jim, you know - he was and - oh he was one of her favourites and 
he was a good scholar too you know, and she was - she was very keen on him, I know that very well. And on the - you know, she wouldn't cross the vicar's children, to be honest too. No. But - she had a nephew there, she couldn't do as she liked with him, h
e
'd cheek her back you know, I remember him having a good hiding with her, and he was - he was kept in you know from play and all, and we used to go to the window and laugh at him, well we'd watch ourselves after when he'd come out I can tell you. We were 
afraid of him.
