Well - they had to like it then didn't they, there was nothing else really. They had to go to colliery and there was nothing else - there, he was a hardworking - man, very - very hardworking, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Do you think he liked it or disliked it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 
Well I never heard him grumbling anyway. He was a very good worker, all the - managers used to say that about him. A very good worker. And as I say they had to like it, there was nothing else - for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 You were telling me about that incident when you were courting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 
Oh - I remember of course - many little things of course we used to go over - and - I thought you would like to hear when we were courting, an
d of course our parents, especially my mother - she didn't want us to go with anyone really, and - and they were - very - cautious now, thinking who we'd have, like we all are isn't it, want the best too four our - children, and she was like that, and of 
c
ourse never come in, but I was - I was ill, very ill, I was about a month in bed, and of course - he was very anxious to come to see me, but wasn't allowed, and of course I'd never asked of course 'cos I know it would be no. But - after I'd been in bed ab
o
ut a fortnight or three weeks - I used to send him notes with my brother, and he used to send notes for me with my brothers, but my cousin now that stayed with us arranged one Sunday night - that after my mother would go to chapel, that he should - come i
n and see me. So he did. And of course - he was very pleased to see me, and yet you know, upset of course, and - so that's how he came to see me when I was ill. Mm. Yes. Mm.
