\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 How would they get the black for the mourning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Well, you know - well I remember one drape
r - used to live in Cwmavon, that he used to come up you know for orders and things like that. My mother bought a lot of them quite a lot of them. You know in everything then, but they'd have the mourning off him I suppose then. I don't remember, no, the 
C
o-op didn't sell anything then did they at the - no clothes. And you know there were packmen coming round there wasn't it. Oh I remember one that came to me now, Mr Sherries, Sherry, and you used to go - give him a little order, well then, when the boys w
ere home - John Griffiths you know, tailor - now he was coming over, and measuring the boys you know, of course like that. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 There was one thing I meant to have asked you too when we were talking about the choir. In the village you know because you e
njoyed that didn't you very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Oh - very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1779283 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Did all the dominations belong to the choir in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1661656 OP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11094101\charrsid12984966 Yes. Yes. And we had a united gamanfa - for - fifty years I think, twenty-five - fifty - yes, fifty years.
